        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 24 at 1:59PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 159 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles south of Thurman, or 28 miles northeast of Limon, moving
southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Arriba.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
